‘He broke free of them, lunged across the dancefloor, grabbed hold of the other man’s head and then wrestled him out of the grip of the bouncers, pulled him to the floor and then got on top of him.’

The alleged biting was not captured on CCTV but Mr Woolcott was said to have been left with blood streaming from the wound as Ball left the club on Old Broad Street near Liverpool Street train station.

