Mr Woolcott has since had to have a skin graft to repair the damage, the court was told.

Ball initially told police that the attack was carried out by somebody else but now accepts he was responsible for the injury and claims he acted in self-defence, it was said.

Mr Gadsden added: ‘The Crown say that is completely wrong.’  Ball denies inflicting grievous bodily harm with intent and the lesser alternative of inflicting grievous bodily harm. The trial continues.

